<paragraph id="8B8A36F56044E61E3E0CFDCEFD5B663D" blockId="1.[262,647,541,565]" box="[262,647,541,565]" pageId="1" pageNumber="285">
<heading id="D0C281996044E61E3E0CFDCEFD5B663D" bold="true" box="[262,647,541,565]" centered="true" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="1" pageNumber="285" reason="2">
<taxonomicName id="4C354D766044E61E3E0CFDCEFD5B663D" authority="Kerremans, 1903" authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1903" box="[262,647,541,565]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Brachycoraebus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="285" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B941EAE76044E61E3E0CFDCEFD5B663D" bold="true" box="[262,647,541,565]" pageId="1" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis id="B941EAE76044E61E3E0CFDCEFE65663D" bold="true" box="[262,441,541,565]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="285">Brachycoraebus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFA44B046044E61E3EC8FDCEFD5B663D" author="Kerremans C" box="[450,647,541,565]" pageId="1" pageNumber="285" pagination="49 - 338" refId="ref4394" refString="Kerremans C (1903) Coleoptera Serricornia, Fam. Buprestidae. In: P. Wytsman. (Ed.). Genera Insectorum, Fasc. 12 b; 12 c; 12 d. Verteneuil &amp; Desmet, Bruxelles, pp. 49 - 338." type="book chapter" year="1903">Kerremans, 1903</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8A36F56044E61E3F82FD8EFE70679D" blockId="1.[134,776,605,917]" pageId="1" pageNumber="285">
Generally, this genus is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D766044E61E3D4AFD8EFF02669D" authority="Gory &amp; Laporte" authorityName="Gory &amp; Laporte" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Coraebus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="285" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B941EAE76044E61E3D4AFD8EFD74667D" box="[576,680,605,629]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="285">Coraebus</emphasis>
Gory &amp; Laporte
</taxonomicName>
, but as the name suggests, it is distinguished from the latter by the body being shorter and wider (2.2 – 2.5 × longer than wide) and more flattened above. For detailed information about taxonomy of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D766044E61E3D58FD0EFD2366FD" authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1903" box="[594,767,733,757]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Brachycoraebus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="285" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B941EAE76044E61E3D58FD0EFD2366FD" box="[594,767,733,757]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="285">Brachycoraebus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, see (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA44B046044E61E3FB2FD2EFE8F671D" author="Kuban V" box="[184,339,765,789]" pageId="1" pageNumber="285" pagination="1 - 37" refId="ref4485" refString="Kuban V (1995 a) Palaearctic and Oriental Coraebini (Coleoptera: Buprestidae) Part I. Entomological Problems, 26 (1): 1 - 37." type="journal article" year="1995">Kubáň, 1995a</bibRefCitation>
). Note that the sexual dimorphism in this genus can be quite significant; for instance, 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D766044E61E3D79FCCDFD04673D" baseAuthorityName="Kerremans" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[627,728,797,821]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Brachycoraebus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="285" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis id="B941EAE76044E61E3D79FCCDFD04673D" box="[627,728,797,821]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="285">B. viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has distinct differences in colouration and ornamentation between the sexes (the female was described as a new species 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D766044E61E3DE5FC8DFF26679D" baseAuthorityName="Kerremans" baseAuthorityYear="1900" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Brachycoraebus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="285" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picturellus">
<emphasis id="B941EAE76044E61E3DE5FC8DFF26679D" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="285">B. picturellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Kerremans).
</paragraph>
